You are working on an existing Laravel HRMS (Human Resource Management System) that uses Livewire for frontend interactivity.

Some modules are already implemented.
Your responsibility is to design, implement, complete, and integrate all remaining HRMS modules using Laravel + Livewire, following enterprise-level standards.

This application must scale for:

Multiple companies (SaaS-ready)

Thousands of employees

Complex compliance & payroll rules

Long-term maintenance by multiple developers

🧠 CORE ARCHITECTURAL RULES (MANDATORY)

Root-cause fixes only

Never add temporary or patch fixes

Refactor poor design when discovered

Livewire is NOT business logic

Livewire components handle:

UI state

User interaction

Emitting events

Business logic MUST live in:

Service classes

Actions / Use-cases

Domain layer

Thin Controllers

Controllers only:

Route requests

Handle auth

Delegate to services or Livewire

Livewire component structure

One responsibility per component

Prefer page components + child components

Avoid monolithic Livewire classes

Database-first design

Proper normalization

Foreign keys & indexes

Soft deletes where applicable

Audit logs for sensitive actions

Security & Authorization

Role-based access control (RBAC)

Permission-based module access

Policies & Gates (never in Livewire views)

Company-level data isolation

Consistency

Follow existing folder & naming conventions

Reuse patterns already present in the project

